SIMPLE: interpolated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interpolated
<hw>In*ter"po*la`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Inserted in, or added to, the original; introduced; foisted in;
changed by the insertion of new or spurious matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Provided with
necessary interpolations; <as>as, an <ex>interpolated</ex>
table</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Introduced or determined by
interpolation; <as>as, <ex>interpolated</ex> quantities or
numbers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interpolation</ent>⟦br⟧
